Kano State governor, Dr. Abdullahi Umar Ganduje on Monday appointed his erstwhile Chief of staff, Alhaji Usman Bala Muhammad as the new Head of service. Until his appointment, Usman Bala Muhammad was a Permanent Secretary with the Ministry of Information. Ganduje’s appointment as the Head of the service coincides with the appointment of three new permanent secretaries. The Permanent Secretaries are Engineer Muhammad Bello Shehu, who was until this new appointment was Director Research and Statistics with Kano Roads Maintenance Agency (KARMA), and now newly appointed Permanent Secretary. Magaji Lawan, who was also, until his new appointment as Permanent Secretary, was Director Final Accounts, Ministry of Finance, Bilyaminu Gambo Zubairu who was also Director PHC, Rano Zonal Office, is now a newly appointed Permanent Secretary. Mairo Audi Dambatta, who was until her new appointment, was Director in the Office of the Head of Service, is now a Permanent Secretary. A statement by Abba Anwar, Chief Press Secretary to the Governor of Kano State saidAll the appointments are with immediate effect.” Anwar quoted his principal to have congratulated them for the newly assigned responsibilities, as he similarly enjoined them to always work hard for the promotion of good virtues in the public service. POLL He added that “You must take it as part of your responsibilities, employing IT-based techniques in your day to day official engagements. You must also bear in mind that, it was your proven track records that uplift you to present spaces. Hence all eyes will be on you to see how you will navigate through.”